HEADWORD: Watchhouse
<hw>Watch"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Watchhouses</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A house in
which a watch or guard is placed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where persons under temporary arrest by the
police of a city are kept; a police station; a lockup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Watchmaker</ent>⟦br⟧
